## API Integration

### Zoom OAuth Flow

1. User clicks "Connect Zoom"
2. Redirects to Zoom authorization
3. Callback exchanges code for access token
4. Token stored in localStorage
5. Real Zoom meetings created via API

### Gmail Invitations

1. User signs in with Google (Gmail scope)
2. OAuth token obtained
3. Calendar invites sent via Gmail API
4. Participants receive email with .ics attachment

## Security Notes

- Client secrets handled on backend only
- OAuth tokens stored in localStorage
- Environment variables for sensitive data
- Never commit `.env` to repository

## Troubleshooting

### "Invalid client_id"
- Verify `.env` file exists in project root
- Check variable names start with `REACT_APP_`
- Restart both servers after changes

### Zoom connection fails
- Ensure redirect URI matches in Zoom app settings
- Clear localStorage and reconnect
- Verify scopes are added in Zoom app

### Email invites not working
- Confirm Gmail API is enabled
- Check OAuth consent screen configuration
- Verify user is added as test user

